Cominco Ltd said itplans to issue units in Canada containing common share purchasewarrants indexed to zinc and copper prices.    Each unit will consist of one deferred retractableredeemable share and one warrant, which will be indexed toaverage market prices of zinc and copper on the exercise date.    Issue size, timing and terms have not yet been determined.    Cominco said it would use proceeds to reduce bank loans andother short-term debt. Underwriters are Nesbitt Thomson DeaconInc, Dominion Securities Inc and Pemberton Houston WilloughbyBell Gouinlock Inc. Reuter&#3;